# To Build Linus Kernel and Install

1. Copy config file from main kernel /boot/config-`uname -r` to build direcotry as ".config"
2. build kernel using "make -jX" - Where X is the number of threads (use 2-4)
3. Install Kernel using "sudo make modules_install install"


# Building subdirectory
make -j2 <path/to/dir> <enable config_ switches>